From: CJ Damsleth <kim@damsleth.no>
Subject: [PATCH 2/2] pmdomain: apple: Handle T6041 raw-boot state

T6041 raw boot leaves core firmware resources active. It also has two
external-display CPU domains which reject the generic AUTO_ENABLE write.

The exact minimum was isolated on a T6040 J614s with the full 214-domain
hierarchy: preserve domains that firmware left active and skip auto-enable
only for dispext0_cpu and dispext1_cpu. Keep the separately inaccessible
disp_cpu domain disabled in the device tree.

Select that behavior from the T6041 compatible. Keep the bring-up property
handling so older experimental device trees continue to work.

Signed-off-by: CJ Damsleth <kim@damsleth.no>
---
 drivers/pmdomain/apple/pmgr-pwrstate.c | 12 ++++++++++--
 1 file changed, 10 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/pmdomain/apple/pmgr-pwrstate.c b/drivers/pmdomain/apple/pmgr-pwrstate.c
--- a/drivers/pmdomain/apple/pmgr-pwrstate.c
+++ b/drivers/pmdomain/apple/pmgr-pwrstate.c
@@ -248,6 +248,5 @@ static int apple_pmgr_ps_probe(struct platform_device *pdev)
 
 	ps->dev = dev;
-	ps->skip_auto_enable = of_property_read_bool(node, "apple,skip-auto-enable");
 	ps->regmap = regmap;
 
 	ret = of_property_read_string(node, "label", &name);
@@ -257,6 +256,13 @@ static int apple_pmgr_ps_probe(struct platform_device *pdev)
 		return ret;
 	}
 
+	/* T6041 raw boot firmware locks auto-PM on the display CPU domains. */
+	ps->skip_auto_enable =
+		of_property_read_bool(node, "apple,skip-auto-enable") ||
+		(of_device_is_compatible(node, "apple,t6041-pmgr-pwrstate") &&
+		 (!strcmp(name, "dispext0_cpu") ||
+		  !strcmp(name, "dispext1_cpu")));
+
 	ret = of_property_read_u32(node, "reg", &ps->offset);
 	if (ret < 0) {
 		dev_err(dev, "missing reg property\n");
@@ -284,5 +290,7 @@ static int apple_pmgr_ps_probe(struct platform_device *pdev)
 		ps->externally_clocked = true;
 
 	active = apple_pmgr_ps_is_active(ps);
-	if (active && of_property_read_bool(node->parent, "apple,preserve-active"))
+	/* T6041 raw boot has no earlier OS stage to quiesce firmware-owned domains. */
+	if (active && (of_property_read_bool(node->parent, "apple,preserve-active") ||
+		       of_device_is_compatible(node, "apple,t6041-pmgr-pwrstate")))
 		ps->genpd.flags |= GENPD_FLAG_ALWAYS_ON;
